    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Competitor Price Monitor with AI-Powered Alerts",
        "height": 80,
        "width": 840,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "34617b7d-1f30-43b4-ab7b-6a4f3c9a2ebf",
      "name": "Note: Title",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1264,
        112
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Overview\nWhen the schedule triggers every 12 hours, this workflow monitors competitor prices and alerts on significant changes:\n\n1. Fetches active competitor URLs from Google Sheets\n2. Scrapes each competitor product page with Firecrawl\n3. Extracts structured product data using an AI agent\n4. Compares competitor price against your own WooCommerce price\n5. Checks for significant changes vs history and sends email alerts if thresholds are crossed",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 380,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "3c96a2a7-20c7-419c-b63d-f812e1a357f7",
      "name": "Note: Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1120,
        432
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Node-by-node Purpose\n\n1. Schedule Trigger - Every 12h\nKicks off the workflow twice daily on a fixed schedule.\n\n2. Get Competitor URLs\nReads active competitor rows from the CompetitorURLs Google Sheet.\n\n3. Loop Over Competitor URLs\nProcesses one competitor URL at a time in a batch loop.\n\n4. Scrape Competitor Page (Firecrawl)\nCalls Firecrawl API to scrape the product page into markdown and product format.\n\n5. IF: Scrape Succeeded?\nChecks if Firecrawl returned success. If yes, proceed to AI extraction. If no, log the failure.\n\n6. Code: Tag Scrape Failure\nClassifies the error type (rate limit, auth, timeout) and captures context.\n\n7. Log Failed Scrape\nWrites failure details to the FailedScrapes sheet for review.\n\n8. AI Agent: Extract Product Data\nUses GPT-4o-mini to parse price, title, SKU, stock status and shipping cost from scraped content.\n\n9. Structured Output Parser: Extraction\nEnforces a JSON schema on the AI output for consistent downstream processing.\n\n10. Code: Reconcile & Normalize\nMerges deterministic Firecrawl data with AI-extracted fields and normalizes the record.\n\n11. Get Our Price (WooCommerce REST)\nLooks up your own product price by SKU via the WooCommerce REST API.\n\n12. Code: Merge Our Price + Diff\nCalculates the percentage difference between your price and the competitor price.\n\n13. Get Latest Snapshot\nReads the previous price record from the LatestSnapshot sheet by match key.\n\n14. Code: Calculate Change vs History\nCompares current scrape to previous snapshot and flags significant changes.\n\n15. IF: Crossed Alert Threshold?\nRoutes significant changes to the alert composer, or bypasses if nothing notable changed.\n\n16. AI Agent: Compose Alert Decision\nUses GPT-4o-mini to catch false positives and compose an actionable alert message.\n\n17. IF: Send Alert?\nRoutes to Gmail if the AI approves sending, or flags as suppressed if deemed a false positive.\n\n18. Send Price Drop Alert\nSends an HTML email to the store owner with competitor details and recommended action.\n\n19. Log to PriceHistory\nAppends the full record to the PriceHistory sheet for audit and trend analysis.\n\n20. Upsert Latest Snapshot\nUpdates or inserts the latest price and stock status into the LatestSnapshot sheet.\n\n21. Send Run Summary / Error Alert\nEmails a run summary pointing to the FailedScrapes and PriceHistory sheets.",
        "height": 964,
        "width": 680,
        "color": 2
      },
      "id": "5347e13c-0419-462c-967c-929841c2ccfc",
      "name": "Note: Node-by-node",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        4016,
        272
      ]
    }
